A First Amendment organization has chimed in on the University of California system’s recent “guidance” forbidding use of terms like “Chinese virus,” saying officials need to rethink their approach.
Refer to the virus as either “COVID-19” or “coronavirus” in both oral and written communications.
From FIRE’s statement:The UC System is a public university system bound by the First Amendment.
UC may certainly take a “more speech” approach to addressing inclusivity on its campus during this unprecedented moment in history.
